<h2>Queries</h2>

<p>Give MScanner examples of the kinds of articles you are looking for,
and it will automatically find similar articles</p>

<ul>
<li>Click on "Query" above</li>
<li>Paste a list of PubMed IDs</li>
<li>Enter a name for the submission</li>
<li>Click "submit"</li>
</ul>

<p>
You will be taken to a refreshing status page until the results
are ready.  View <a href="static/sample/pg07-query">sample results</a>
for a query using 1,500 citations from the 
<a href="http://www.pharmgkb.org">Pharmacogenetics KnowledgeBase</a>.
</p>

<h3>Cross validation</h3> 

<p> 
Using random articles for input produces random articles for output. To see
how good MScanner is at distinguishing the input from the rest of <a
href="http://www.nlm.nih.gov/pubs/factsheets/medline.html">Medline</a>, use the
10-fold cross validation option on the query page (requires 30 or more training
citations). View <a href="static/sample/pg07-valid"> sample cross validation
output</a> 
</p>

<p>
MScanner has been tested using Mozilla Firefox and Internet Explorer 7,
and the mini-application for searching within the output page
requires JavaScript to be enabled.
</p>

